   <title class="- topic/title " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_cts_configuring.xml" xtrc="title:1;13:26">Configuring CTS</title>
   <body class="- topic/body " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_cts_configuring.xml" xtrc="body:1;16:24">
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_cts_configuring.xml" xtrc="p:1;19:21">CTS can be configured with a user-defined completion timeout value which is made up of a Timeout Multiplier and a Timeout Base. The total timeout is provided as:</p>
      <codeblock xml:space="preserve" class="+ topic/pre pr-d/codeblock " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_cts_configuring.xml" xtrc="codeblock:1;20:201">CTS_Timeout_Value = CTS_Completion_Timeout_Multiple * CTS_Completion_Timeout_Base</codeblock>
      <p class="- topic/p " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_cts_configuring.xml" xtrc="p:2;23:21">When a completion timeout is detected as specified by the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_cts_configuring.xml" xtrc="i:1;25:24">CTS_Timeout_Value</i>, firmware will be notified to synthesize a completion.</p>
      <note class="- topic/note " xtrf="C:\Git\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\XDocs-DITA-OT-185\DITA-OT1.8.5\samples\diffed\_b-0-file-\Trident\device\devspec\error_handling\trident_error_handling_cts_configuring.xml" xtrc="note:1;28:27">PCI Express Base Specification Revision 4.0 notes that the Host Completion Timeout Value should be at least 10ms. The CTS Timeout Value must be set lower than the Host’s Completion Timeout Value. A safe value for CTS Timeout is around 10ms below the host timeout. For small host timeouts, CTS can be set to ½ of the Host Timeout value. For example, if the Host Completion Timeout Value is 50ms, the switch USP CTS Timeout value should be 40ms.</note>
   </body>
